\item[2.] {\bf Re-ranking} passages by various criteria. We present two techniques to prioritize passages based on (i) {\bf num:} number of {\em named-entity mentions} in a passage, to leverage co-occurrences of multiple O values for the same predicate
 (e.g., a passage about several friends), and (ii) {\bf amp:} pseudo-relevance feedback [DBLP:journals/ftir/Zhai08] to {\em amplify} signals from best passages to refine the prompt for the next round.